<item>
            <title>[LU-13157] migrate symlink with target name length &gt; 59 cause crash</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13157</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;mdd_migrate() allocate &apos;la_size + 1&apos; for symlink target name, the extra &apos;+1&apos; is a mistake, which will cause read beyond range fault: if target name is 59 bytes long, then it will try to read target name from external block other than inline i_block&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;15&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, that&apos;s why when target name is shorter than 59 it won&apos;t cause any problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
